---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const lastUpdated = 'April 6, 2025';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | ConstructionCalc"
  description="Cookie policy for ConstructionCalc.com — what cookies we use and how you can control them."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-navy-900 mb-2">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-6 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">1. What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that a website stores on your device when you visit. They are widely
          used to make websites work, to work more efficiently, and to provide information to the website owner.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">2. How we use cookies</h2>
        <p>ConstructionCalc uses a minimal set of cookies and browser storage to provide a functional experience:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Consent preference (localStorage):</strong> We store your cookie consent choice
            (key: <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">cookie_consent</code>) locally in your
            browser so we do not ask you again on subsequent visits. This data never leaves your device.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>No tracking or analytics cookies:</strong> We do not use cookies for analytics,
            advertising, or user tracking. All calculations are performed entirely in your browser.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>No third-party cookies:</strong> We do not embed third-party scripts, ad networks,
            or social media widgets that would place cookies on your device.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">3. Types of cookies we use</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-2">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 rounded-md">
            <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-600 uppercase text-xs">
              <tr>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Name</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Type</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="odd:bg-white even:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">cookie_consent</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-2">Necessary</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-2">Stores your cookie consent choice to avoid repeated prompts.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-2">Persistent (localStorage)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">4. Hosting provider</h2>
        <p>
          This site is hosted on <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (GitHub, Inc., a Microsoft subsidiary).
          GitHub may collect standard server-side logs (IP address, browser user agent, referring URL, timestamp)
          as part of their infrastructure operations. This is outside our control and governed by
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
             class="text-brand-600 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's Privacy Statement</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">5. Managing and withdrawing consent</h2>
        <p>You can manage or withdraw your cookie consent at any time using any of the following methods:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Clear browser storage:</strong> Open your browser's developer tools (F12 &rarr; Application
            &rarr; Local Storage) and delete the <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">cookie_consent</code> key.
            The consent banner will reappear on your next visit.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear all site data:</strong> Use your browser's built-in option to clear cookies and
            site data for this domain.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Browser settings:</strong> Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies through
            their privacy or security settings.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">6. Your rights under GDPR</h2>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have the right to access, rectify, or erase
          any personal data we hold, and to object to or restrict its processing. Since ConstructionCalc stores
          no personal data on our servers, there is nothing for us to provide or delete. For any questions,
          contact us at <a href="mailto:franruizlozano31@gmail.com" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline">franruizlozano31@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">7. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. Changes will be published on this page with
          an updated date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions about this Cookie Policy, please contact:
          <a href="mailto:franruizlozano31@gmail.com" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline">franruizlozano31@gmail.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-slate-200">
      <a href={`${base}/`} class="text-brand-600 hover:underline text-sm">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
